{"type":"message","id":"c834e3e8","parentId":"47588638","timestamp":"2026-05-26T07:31:00.340Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the issue was clear - the Unity batch mode ran `git pull` inside the pipeline and it failed at some point (git pull errors). But the overall exit code was still 0 because the Unity batch mode completed \"successfully\" even though individual steps had errors.\n\nThe user is asking: can we detect when the build compilation (hot update pipeline) fails and give a proper error notification instead of a success message?\n\nThe key issues:\n1. The Unity exit code was 0 even though the pipeline had failures (git pull failed within the pipeline)\n2. The sub-agent checked Unity's exit code but Unity batch mode exits with 0 even when some steps fail\n\nI need to improve the hot update pipeline to:\n1. After Unity exits, check the log file for error patterns (like \"LogError\", \"失败\", etc.)\n2. If errors are found, send a failure notification instead of success\n3. Notify the owner (主人) immediately when failure is detected\n\nLet me first understand the current approach. The bat file calls Unity in batchmode, and the sub-agent checks the exit code. But Unity's exit code is 0 even when the pipeline script encounters errors internally (like git pull failing).\n\nThe best approach is:\n1. After the Unity process exits, grep the log for critical error indicators\n2. If errors found → send failure notification to group + notify owner\n3. If no errors → send success notification\n\nLet me improve the process. I should update:\n- The instructions in TOOLS.md for the hot update pipeline\n- Also update the sub-agent spawn template to include error checking logic\n\nActually, let me think about what the best place to fix this is. The sub-agent is created each time and given instructions. I should update the instructions/template so the next sub-agent properly detects failures.\n\nBut I could also create a wrapper script that:\n1. Runs the bat file\n2. Checks the exit code\n3. Also checks the log for errors\n4. Returns a proper exit code\n\nOr I could just update the instructions in TOOLS.md and MEMORY.md to include this check in the sub-agent's task instructions.\n\nLet me think about what the best approach is...\n\nThe simplest and most robust approach:\n1. Update TOOLS.md/MEMORY.md to add a step in the hot update process\n2. After Unity exits, scan the log for errors using a PowerShell command\n3. If errors found (non-trivial ones, not just licensing warnings), treat as failure\n\nLet me also check what pattern would be reliable. The key error indicators in the log:\n- \"git更新失败\" - git pull failed\n- Unity compile errors (CS\\d+ errors)\n- Build step failures\n\nLet me create a comprehensive check.\n\nActually, I think the best approach is to update the task template that the sub-agent uses. The sub-agent task description is in TOOLS.md under \"更新测试服（客户端热更）\" and also MEMORY.md.\n\nLet me update the instructions to add post-build error checking.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"看到了！这次的日志里虽然 Unity 退出码是 0，但流水线内部有 **git pull 失败** 的错误（\"git更新失败，请手动拉新\"）。所以 Unity 在 batchmode 下即使有步骤失败，退出码还是 0。\n\n让我改进流程，加入编译失败检测逻辑。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_HIyDiPAQVVJxsjB0h4Nk0216","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"powershell -Command \"Select-String -Path 'E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log' -Pattern '(error CS\\d+|git更新失败|Build completed with|BuildFailed|编译失败)' -Encoding UTF8 | Select-Object -First 20\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":2088,"output":818,"cacheRead":27648,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30554,"cost":{"input":0.00029232,"output":0.00022904000000000002,"cacheRead":0.0007741439999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0012955039999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779780647834,"responseId":"81e392ed-f5f6-4c08-aa0e-f34aee7812