{"type":"message","id":"0df45a5b","parentId":"10b6639a","timestamp":"2026-05-26T07:31:29.806Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I also need to update the sub-agent spawn task template. The spawn template is inline when I call sessions_spawn. Since it's not persisted in a file, the next time the sub-agent runs, I'll update the task description to include the error checking step.\n\nBut actually, the sub-agent task description in the spawn call is generated fresh each time, so I just need to make sure I update the template for next time. The instructions are now updated in TOOLS.md and MEMORY.md which I read when constructing the task.\n\nAlso, I should check - the current log already had failures. Let me look at the exact patterns that would be most reliable for detection. The log has:\n\n1. `git更新失败，请手动拉新` - clearly an error from git pull\n2. `UnityEngine.Debug:LogError` - but this is a stack trace, not very specific\n\nThe key thing is the `LogError` pattern might catch too many false positives since some LogErrors are just git pull warnings.\n\nActually, looking more carefully, the specific errors are:\n- `git更新失败，请手动拉新` - this is the actual error message logged by the pipeline\n- `error CS\\d+:` - this is C# compilation errors\n\nThe `LogError` and `Exception` would be too broad. Let me narrow it to only meaningful errors.\n\nActually, looking at the pipeline output, the `LogError` calls in the log ARE the git pull failure (line 653 calls LogError, then line 667 prints \"git更新失败\"). So checking `LogError` would correctly flag this.\n\nBut `LogError` could be false positive for non-critical errors. Let me think...\n\nActually the safest approach is:\n1. First check Unity exit code - if non-zero, immediate failure\n2. Then scan for specific Chinese error messages + C# compile errors\n3. `LogError` might be too broad\n\nLet me refine the error checking approach. I'll check for:\n- `error CS\\d+:` - C# compile errors (hard failures)\n- `git更新失败` - git pull failure\n- Specific build failure markers\n\nAnd use the Unity exit code as a secondary signal. But actually the problem IS that Unity exits with 0 even on failure, so exit code isn't reliable.\n\nLet me just keep the check simple and focused on what we actually saw fail:\n- `error CS\\d+:`\n- `git更新失败`\n\nThese are concrete, actionable failures that we know happen.\n\nActually, let me keep it broader with `LogError` too, but just note that we should review it. The sub-agent can use judgment. Let me update the TOOLS.md more precisely.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Actually，`LogError` 和 `Exception` 的范围太宽了，让我聚焦到真正有意义的错误检测模式上。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_0kSjPe5KG0vkvoe1bG4j1660","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\TOOLS.md","edits":[{"oldText":"**编译失败检测逻辑：**\n- Unity 退出码为 0 不代表流水线完全成功（流水线内部步骤可能失败但 Unity 仍以 0 退出）\n- 必须扫描日志文件的以下关键字：`error CS\\d+`（C#编译报错）、`git更新失败`（git pull 失败）、`LogError`（流水线步骤抛出错误）、`Exception`（未处理异常）\n- 检查命令：`powershell -Command \"Select-String -Path 'BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log' -Pattern 'error CS\\d+|git更新失败|LogError|Exception'\"`\n- 匹配到关键字 → 视为失败，发失败通知\n- 无匹配 + Unity 退出码 0 → 视为成功，发成功通知","newText":"**编译失败检测逻辑：**\n- ⚠️ **Unity 退出码为 0 不代表流水线完全成功！** 流水线内部步骤可能失败（如 git pull），但 Unity 仍以 0 退出\n- 必须额外扫描日志文件，检测以下致命错误：\n  - `error CS\\d+:` — C# 编译报错（硬错误）\n  - `git更新失败` — 流水线内 git pull 失败\n  - `Build completed with.*errors` — Unity 构建统计有 errors\n- 检查命令：`powershell -Command \"Select-String -Path 'E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log' -Pattern 'error CS\\d+:|git更新失败|Build completed with'\"`\n- 匹配到关键字 → **视为失败**，发失败通知（hotupdate-fail）\n- 无匹配 + Unity 退出码 0 → **视为成功**，发成功通知（hotupdate-ok）"}]}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":68,"output":1081,"cacheRead":31872,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33021,"cost":{"input":0.00000952,"output":0.00030268,"cacheRead":