{"type":"message","id":"342fa0fb","parentId":"af90c1f4","timestamp":"2026-05-26T07:34:56.917Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the Luban config system. Looking at `Common.xlsx`:\n\nThe xlsx file format is:\n- Row 1 (header): `##column#var`, `##type`, `##group`, more columns for separator/cellType\n- Row 2 (comment/description headers): empty, empty, empty, 描述, 具体参数\n- Row 3+ (data rows): Column A = field name (`##var`), Column B = field type (`##type`), and then the data\n\nWait, looking at the CSV output more carefully, the columns seem to be:\n- First column: field name (##column#var header with value like `BattleStartSelectTime`)\n- Second column: field type (##type header with value like `int`)\n- Third column: group (##group header, sometimes empty or `c`)\n- Fourth column: description (like \"发牌时长\")\n- Fifth column: default value (like \"30\")\n\nWait, this is a key-value config table (CommonConfig), not a typical list table. Let me check a list-style table like Card.xlsx or an actual data table.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_QhwkOMjBFXnmMZVQx3bo9341","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cmd /c \"cd /d E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\config\\SoloConfig && xlsx2csv\\xlsx2csv.exe Datas\\Card.xlsx 2>nul\"","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":5161,"output":344,"cacheRead":42752,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48257,"cost":{"input":0.00072254,"output":0.00009632000000000001,"cacheRead":0.001197056,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.002015916}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779780892192,"responseId":"0c769254-18d3-4825-91aa-466d969a94b3"}}
{"type":"message","id":"94467b8b","parentId":"342fa0fb","timestamp":"2026-05-26T07:34:57.413Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_QhwkOMjBFXnmMZVQx3bo9341","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"##var,id,type,name,buff,desc,icon,chessIcon,attribute,Clan,deck,deckDesc,rare,cost,attack,life,cardPool,target,targetProps,keyword,keyword_value,global_id,global_num,entrance_effect,attack_effect,career,voice_in,voice_dead\r\r\n##type,int,int,string,\"(list#sep=,),int\",string,string,string,int,\"(list#sep=,),int\",int,\"(list#sep=|),string\",int,int,int,int,\"(list#sep=,),int\",int,\"(list#sep=,),int\",\"(list#sep=,),int\",string,\"(list#sep=,),string\",\"(list#sep=,),int\",string,string,string,int,int\r\r\n##group,\"c,s\",\"c,s\",\"c,s\",\"c,s\",c,c,c,\"c,s\",\"c,s\",\"c,s\",c,\"c,s\",\"c,s\",\"c,s\",\"c,s\",\"c,s\",\"c,s\",\"c,s\",\"c,s\",\"c,s\",\"c,s\",\"c,s\",c,c,c,c,c\r\r\n##,这是id,卡牌类型（1：随从，2：咒术，3：反制）,名字,buff,卡牌描述,图标,棋子图标,\"属性（1:暗,2:风,3:光,4:火,5:金属,6:木,7:水,8:岩）\",\"种族（1: 恶魔,2:霍普,3:机械,4:龙,5:人类,6:树人,7:巫师,8:吸血鬼,9:野兽,10:幽灵,11:海盗,12:精灵）\",套牌,相关卡牌,稀有度（1：白色，2：绿色，3：蓝色，4：紫色，5：橙色）,费用,攻击力,血量,所属牌池,目标（本表备注）,目标参数,关键字,关键字参数,全局数据id,全局数据值,入场特效相关,攻击特效相关,生涯,入场语音,死亡语音\r\r\n,1010001,1,恶魔公主黑天鹅,101000101,<color=#3D53AE>限二</color>。<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：使1个友方<color=#B92661>恶魔暴君</color>获得<color=#3D53AE>穿透</color>，<color=#3D53AE>疯狂</color>，并移除无法攻击,emogongzhuheitiane,emogongzhuheitiane_s,1,5,2,2|101,5,3,3,3,2,1,\"3,101\",\"28,1,19,7\",,,,,,谁都想找到她，包括弥达斯本人。,,400001\r\r\n,1010002,1,吸血鬼领主,101000201,<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：若你的手牌中有<color=#B92661>深渊统御</color>，则消灭1个敌方随从，<color=#3D53AE>恶魔暴君弥达斯</color>获得被消灭随从的属性,xixueguilingzhu,xixueguilingzhu_s,1,8,,2,5,2,3,1,2,3,,1,,shoupaibaojun,+1,,,忠诚演绎千百次才能被主人放在心上，而背叛只需要一次。,,\r\r\n,1010003,1,毒蛇女王,101000301,<color=#3D53AE>遗言</color>：从牌组或墓地中抽1张恶魔公主黑天鹅，并使其费用-2,dushenvwang,dushenvwang_s,1,9,2,2,5,2,3,2,2,,,2,,,,,,厄客德娜，小镇上最漂亮的姑娘。毒蛇女王，黑天鹅最忠诚的下属。,,\r\r\n,1010004,1,传教士,101000401,每用1张咒术，你的<color=#3D53AE>恶魔暴君弥达斯</color>获得+2+2,chuanjiaoshi,chuanjiaoshi_s,1,5,2,2,4,2,0,3,2,,,,,,,,,妖言惑众还是深谙圣意？这得弥达斯说了算！,,\r\r\n,1010005,1,灵魂之主,101000501,<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：抽至多2张<color=#3D53AE>索命亡魂</color>，随后将2张<color=#3D53AE>索命亡魂</color>置入牌组,linghunzhizhu,linghunzhizhu_s,1,10,,100,5,3,4,2,3,,,\"1,25\",,,,,,\"忙碌的灵魂主理人，带走他的再夺取她的，很快就轮到你了。\r\n别急，更多亡魂正在赶来的路上。实在等不了了？你的背后刚好就有一只。\",,\r\r\n,1010006,1,灵魂囚徒,101000601,<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：你的牌组中每有1张<color=#3D53AE>索命亡魂</color>，本随从获得+1+1,linghunqiutu,linghunqiutu_s,1,10,,100,5,2,2,2,3,,,\"1,25\",,,,,,一个普通的传奇故事：一名剑士拔出了尘封之剑，他付出了生命的代价。,,\r\r\n,1010007,1,灵魂共鸣者,101000701,<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：将3张<color=#3D53AE>索命亡魂</color>置入牌组,linghungongmingzhe,linghungongmingzhe_s,1,10,,100,4,2,2,3,3,,,\"1,25\",,,,,,最初的最初，他只是想和早逝的女儿说说话。,,\r\r\n,1010008,1,亡魂吹笛者,101000801,<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：本局对战中，你的<color=#3D53AE>索命亡魂</color>伤害+1,wanghunchuidizhe,wanghunchuidizhe_s,1,10,,100,4,2,2,1,3,,,\"1,25\",,,,,,\"“噗噗噗嘟嘟噗。”\r\n“放错配乐了，他吹的可不是卡祖笛！”\",,\r\r\n,1010009,1,亡魂宝箱,101000901,<color=#3D53AE>遗言</color>：将1张<color=#3D53AE>索命亡魂</color>置入牌组,wanghunbaoxiang,wanghunbaoxiang_s,1,10,,100,1,1,1,1,3,,,\"2,25\",,,,,,,,\r\r\n,1010010,1,冥界使者,101001001,<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：将1张<color=#3D53AE>索命亡魂</color>置入牌组,mingjieshizhe,mingjieshizhe_s,1,10,,100,3,1,1,2,3,,,\"1,25\",,,,,,快上船，晚了就来不及救场了！,,\r\r\n,1010011,1,收割者,101001101,<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：抽1张<color=#3D53AE>索命亡魂</color>,shougezhe,shougezhe_s,1,10,,100,3,2,2,1,3,,,\"1,25\",,,,,,是时候进场收割了！嗯？亡魂怎么还在牌库里？,,\r\r\n,1010012,1,躁动灵魂,101001201,每抽到1张<color=#3D53AE>索命亡魂</color>，本随从获得+2+2,zaodonglinghun,zaodonglinghun_s,1,10,,100,3,1,1,1,3,,,25,,,,,,我们需要更多的亡魂，更多！,,\r\r\n,1010013,1,灵魂亵渎者,101001301,<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：从牌组中<color=#3D53AE>移除</color>2张<color=#3D53AE>索命亡魂</color>，随后消灭1个敌方随从,linghunxieduzhe,linghunxieduzhe_s,1,10,,100,4,2,3,3,3,3,,\"1,22,25\",,ghost,+2,,,亡魂不是食物，吃了又吐算是两次亵渎。,,\r\r\n,1010014,1,亡魂的死神,\"6,101001401\",<color=#3D53AE>勇猛</color>。<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：若你的牌组中<color=#3D53AE>索命亡魂</color>≥5，则本随从获得<color=#3D53AE>疯狂</color>,wanghundesishen,wanghundesishen_s,1,10,,100,5,3,6,4,3,,,\"1,25,11,7\",,ghost,+5,,,生者世界里只有领导能够给员工赋能，但在亡者世界里，这件事得反过来做才有用。,,\r\r\n,1010015,1,缚魂棺,101001501,<color=#3D53AE>遗言</color>：抽1张<color=#3D53AE>索命亡魂</color>,fuhunguan,fuhunguan_s,1,10,,100,3,2,3,2,3,,,\"2,25\",,,,,,,,\r\r\n,1010016,1,亡魂乐队,101001601,<color=#3D53AE>遗言</color>：本局对战中，你的<color=#3D53AE>索命亡魂</color>伤害+1,wanghunyuedui,wanghunyuedui_s,1,10,,100,4,2,2,2,3,,,\"2,25\",,,,,,死亡摇滚乐！,,\r\r\n,1010017,1,幽灵船长,101001701,友方每召唤1个随从，本随从获得+1+1,youlingchuanzhang,youlingchuanzhang_s,1,10,,,2,2,0,1,3,,,,,,,,,他总把“飞翔的荷兰人”号念成“灰翔的河南人”号。,,\r\r\n,1010018,1,夺魂者,\"101001801,4\",<color=#3D53AE>疯狂</color>。<color=#3D53AE>击杀</color>：获得+1攻击,duohunzhe,duohunzhe_s,1,10,,,2,3,3,5,3,,,\"7,6\",,,,,,别怕，就像睡着一样，很快就会过去的……,,\r\r\n,1010019,1,游荡灵魂,,,youdanglinghun,youdanglinghun_s,1,10,,,1,2,3,4,3,,,,,,,,,他模糊地记得家乡稻田的模样，那是一种像太阳一样温暖的颜色。,,\r\r\n,1010020,1,无头行者,,,wutouxingzhe,wutouxingzhe_s,1,10,,,1,1,2,3,3,,,,,,,,,与头颅一起弃置的是眼睛，与灵魂一同长存的是意志。,,\r\r\n,1010021,1,掠食之狼,\"101002101,101002102,101002103\",<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：消灭1个友方<color=#B92661>狼人之影</color>，本随从获得+3+3和<color=#3D53AE>穿透</color>,lueshizhilang,lueshizhilang_s,1,9,4,4,5,3,5,4,4,1,\"3,4\",\"1,19\",,zhanchanglangying,+1,,,\"饥饿是他一生的命题。\r\n不挑食，吃嘛嘛香，身体倍棒！\",,\r\r\n,1010022,1,狼王,\"101002201,101002202\",<color=#3D53AE>唯一</color>。<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：若友方墓地中的<color=#B92661>狼人之影</color>≥6，则从中抽3张并使其费用变0,langwang,langwang_s,1,9,4,4,5,3,4,3,4,,,\"4,1\",,mudilangying,+6,,,每一代狼王都有一个使命：统御狼群，向教会复仇。,,\r\r\n,1010023,1,姐姐,\"101002301,101002302,101002303\",<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：使你的<color=#B92661>攻击牌</color>获得强化,jiejie,jiejie_s,1,5,,\"8,-1|9,-1\",5,1,2,2,2,,,1,,,,,,长大以后就能成为姐姐吗？就是那种强大的，温柔的，有能量的人。,,\r\r\n,1010024,1,弥达斯-化身,101002401,此牌视为<color=#3D53AE>恶魔暴君弥达斯</color>，若本牌在你的手牌中，你每使用1张<color=#B92661>攻击牌</color>或<color=#B92661>特殊攻击牌</color>，本牌费用-1,emobaojunmidasihuashen,emobaojunmidasihuashen_s,1,\"5,1\",101,\"101|2|8,-1|9,-1\",5,11,1,1,2,,,,,,,Fx_Solo000_Born_Midasi,,,,400000\r\r\n,1010025,1,暗夜占卜师,101002501,<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：从墓地召唤1个<color=#B92661>寒霜教会</color>随从,anyezhanbushi,anyezhanbushi_s,1,7,6,6,5,2,2,2,5,,,1,,,,,,黑暗遮蔽了干扰命运的光，她在此中看到了教会的未来。,,\r\r\n,1010026,1,恶毒诅咒者,101002601,<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：消灭1个友方<color=#B92661>寒霜教会</color>随从，随后对敌方英雄造成3点伤害,eduzuzhouzhe,eduzuzhouzhe_s,1,7,,,2,1,3,2,5,1,\"3,6\",1,,,,,,\"“为什么每个诅咒者都要遮住自己的脸？”\r\n“失去自我这层身份之后，道德约束自动降级了，当然就能像呼吸一样释放最纯粹的恶意了。”\",,\r\r\n,2000097,2,灭世,\"200009701,200009702\",<color=#3D53AE>唯一</color>。消灭场上所有随从,mieshi,,,,,,6,3,,,20001,,,4,,,,,,\"咩事？灭啊？咩？\r\n于是洪水就这么席卷了世界。\",,\r\r\n,200009701,2,灭世,\"200009701,200009702\",<color=#3D53AE>唯一</color>。消灭场上所有随从,mieshi,,,,,,6,3,,,,,,\"4,101\",,,,,,\"咩事？灭啊？咩？\r\n于是洪水就这么席卷了世界。\",,\r\r\n,1010027,1,愤怒之狼,101002701,<color=#3D53AE>遗言</color>：若友方墓地中的<color=#B92661>狼人之影</color>≥4，随机消灭1个敌方随从,fennuzhilang,fennuzhilang_s,1,9,4,4,4,1,2,2,4,,,2,,,,,,人哀其友，物伤其类，狼怒其敌。\r\r\n,1010028,1,狼之影,\"101002801,101002802\",抽到时，所有<color=#3D53AE>野兽</color>获得+1+1；<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：若友方墓地中<color=#B92661>狼人之影</color>≥3，则将本牌置于敌方牌组顶,langzhiying,langzhiying_s,1,9,4,4,3,2,0,7,4,,,1,,mudilangying,+3,,,除了阴谋，狼人也经常蛰伏在阴影之下。\r\r\n,1010029,1,野性狼魂,\"101002901,101002902\",<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：场上所有<color=#B92661>狼人之影</color>获得+1+1,yexinglanghun,yexinglanghun_s,1,9,4,4,1,1,1,1,4,,,1,,,,,,“月光……是我们共同的母亲。”\r\r\n,1010030,1,狼之首领,101003001,若友方墓地中的<color=#B92661>狼人之影</color>≥5，则本牌费用为0,langzhishouling,langzhishouling_s,1,9,4,4,5,3,4,4,4,,,,,,,,,一般来说，狼王必定是狼群的首领，而狼群的首领并不一定是狼王。\r\r\n,1010031,1,月夜咆哮者,\"101003101,101003102\",本随从造成伤害后，获得+1+1，并将牌组中1张费用≤2的<color=#B92661>狼人之影</color>置入墓地,yueyepaoxiaozhe,yueyepaoxiaozhe_s,1,9,4,4,3,2,4,1,4,,,,,,,,,\"“怎么分辨狼人在求偶还是呼唤同伴？”\r\n“假如你是人类的话，他们一定是在呼唤同伴准备撕碎你。”\"\r\r\n,1010032,1,月之灵,101003201,<color=#3D53AE>遗言</color>：从牌组或墓地中抽1张月圆之夜,yuezhiling,yuezhiling_s,1,9,4,4,4,2,3,3,4,,,2,,,,,,\"一只狼崽蹭了蹭母亲还温热的尸体，高枕云端的月神落下了一滴同情的泪水。\r\n泪水化为雨水亲吻着狼崽的额头，他变成了一个人类男孩。\"\r\r\n,1020001,1,风龙,102000101,<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：若场上有其他友方<color=#3D53AE>龙</color>，本随从获得<color=#3D53AE>偷袭</color>,fenglong,fenglong_s,2,4,,,3,1,4,1,1,,,\"1,16\",,zhanchanglong,+1,,,一个头用聊天拉近距离，另一个头趁其不备偷袭。\r\r\n,1020002,1,迅捷之狼,\"102000201,102000202\",<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：若场上有其他<color=#B92661>狼人之影</color>，本随从获得+2+2；若友方墓地中的<color=#B92661>狼人之影</color>≥6，本牌费用变0,xunjiezhilang,xunjiezhilang_s,2,9,4,4,5,2,3,1,4,,,1,,zhanchanglangying,+1,,,狼王最得力的左右手，一爪锦上添花，一爪雪中送炭。\r\r\n,1030009,1,膨胀法师,103000901,<color=#3D53AE>击杀</color>：对敌方英雄造成4点伤害,pengzhangfashi,pengzhangfashi_s,3,7,6,6,5,3,4,6,5,,,6,,,,,,他膨胀了，就变强了。\r\r\n,1020005,1,利爪之狼,102000501,<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：消灭1个友方<color=#B92661>狼人之影</color>，随后随机消灭1个敌方随从,lizhuazhilang,lizhuazhilang_s,2,9,4,4,3,1,1,1,4,1,\"3,4\",1,,zhanchanglangying,+1,,,千万别手滑误食旁边的随从。\r\r\n,1070001,1,时光魔术师,107000101,<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：若场上有友方<color=#B92661>寒霜教会</color>随从，则召唤1个<color=#B92661>寒霜教会</color>随从，该随从本回合无法攻击,shiguangmoshushi,shiguangmoshushi_s,7,\"9,7\",,6,4,2,2,3,5,,,1,,zhanchanghanhui,+1,,,黑森林原本完整的时间线分裂成了八条，他被时间之神外派到此观测变化。\r\r\n,1070003,1,双手施法者,107000301,<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：弃掉手牌中的1张<color=#B92661>冰能魔晶</color>，随后获得<color=#3D53AE>疯狂</color>，<color=#3D53AE>勇猛</color>,shuangshoushifazhe,shuangshoushifazhe_s,7,7,6,6|1,5,3,5,4,5,,,\"1,7,11\",,,,,,其实她觉得单手施法比较帅，但无奈这违背了女巫协会的《萌新女巫守则》。\r\r\n,3000045,3,雾海降临,\"300004501,300004502,300004503\",<color=#3D53AE>唯一</color>。当友方随从被攻击时，立即结束当前回合,wuhaijianglin,,,,,,5,,,,3,,,4,,,,,,可见度：0。\r\r\n,300004501,3,雾海降临,\"300004501,300004502,300004503\",<color=#3D53AE>唯一</color>。当友方随从被攻击时，立即结束当前回合,wuhaijianglin,,,,,,5,,,,,,,\"4,101\",,,,,,可见度：0。\r\r\n,1020009,1,劫掠之狼,,,jieluezhilang,jieluezhilang_s,2,9,4,4,1,2,3,4,4,,,,,,,,,严肃点，不许笑，狼人正在村子里抢劫呢！\r\r\n,1020010,1,狂奔之狼,\"102001001,102001002,102001003\",<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：将墓地中的1张<color=#B92661>狼人之影</color>置入牌组，随后获得+1+1和<color=#3D53AE>疯狂</color>,kuangbenzhilang,kuangbenzhilang_s,2,9,4,4,2,2,3,2,4,,,\"1,7\",,mudilangying,+1,,,同伴的尸体摞在墓地，教会的猎人紧随身后，风在耳边呼啸，仇恨驱使他奔向杀戮。\r\r\n,1030001,1,小王子,\"103000101,6\",<color=#3D53AE>勇猛</color>。<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：如果我方英雄为皇后，使你的<color=#3D53AE>恶魔暴君弥达斯</color>获得+4+4,xiaowangzi,xiaowangzi_s,3,5,2,2,4,1,2,2,2,,,\"11,1\",,,,,,小王子心中的亲情排名：父皇第一，母后第二，最怕姐姐。\r\r\n,1030002,1,剑术导师,103000201,<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：对你的英雄造成5点伤害,jianshudaoshi,jianshudaoshi_s,3,5,2,2,3,2,5,5,2,,,1,,,,,,\"报课加小群，送屠龙宝剑。\r\n某段时间，他的剑术课小广告贴遍了整座王城的角落：屠龙宝剑，报课就送！\"\r\r\n,1030003,1,迷你骑士,103000301,<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：对你的英雄造成3点伤害,miniqishi,miniqishi_s,3,5,2,2,3,1,4,3,2,,,1,,,,,,不好意思，砍错人了。\r\r\n,3000046,3,凝固,\"300004601,300004602\",<color=#3D53AE>唯一</color>。当敌方使用<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>随从时，将<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>效果无效化并消灭该随从,ninggu,,,,,,5,,,,2,,,\"1,4\",,,,,,小红帽，不要乱玩外婆的胶水。\r\r\n,3000048,3,咒语突破,300004801,<color=#3D53AE>唯一</color>。当敌方使用咒术时，使其无效化,zhouyutupo,,,,,,5,,,,3,,,4,,,,,,这是法师们追求的凌驾于一切法术之上的至高境界：直接干涉魔法的编织过程，于起始之处改写结局。\r\r\n,3000049,3,封印,\"300004901,300004902\",当触发敌方反制时，使敌方反制无效,fengyin,,,,,,5,,,,4,,,,,,,,,反弹！反弹你的反弹！\r\r\n,3000055,3,魔法筒,300005501,<color=#3D53AE>唯一</color>。当友方目标被攻击时，中止攻击，随后对敌方英雄造成=攻击随从攻击力的伤害,mofatong,,,,,,5,,,,4,,,4,,,,,,\"*恶毒的诅咒\r\n反弹~\"\r\r\n,300005501,3,魔法筒,300005501,<color=#3D53AE>唯一</color>。当友方目标被攻击时，中止攻击，随后对敌方英雄造成=攻击随从攻击力的伤害,mofatong,,,,,,5,,,,,,,\"4,101\",,,,,,\"*恶毒的诅咒\r\n反弹~\"\r\r\n,1030008,1,外婆,103000801,<color=#3D53AE>遗言</color>：获得2张<color=#B92661>攻击牌</color>,waipo,waipo_s,3,5,,\"8,-1|9,-1\",4,2,2,3,2,,,2,,,,,,孩子，敌人很强大，你需要外婆的帮助……\r\r\n,2000111,2,重新抽牌,200011101,<color=#3D53AE>唯一</color>。弃掉所有手牌，随后抽相同数量的牌,chongxinchoupai,,,,,,5,1,,,4,,,4,,,,,,虽然人生没有重来一次的机会，但你可以随时开启一段新的生活。\r\r\n,1010038,1,冥府巫师,101003801,本随从攻击英雄后，随机<color=#3D53AE>移除</color>敌方墓地中至多3张牌，随后将等量的<color=#3D53AE>索命亡魂</color>置入牌组,mingfuwushi,mingfuwushi_s,1,10,,100,5,2,3,3,3,,,\"22,25\",,,,,,一百三十九岁，是死灵们的偶像。\r\r\n,1040001,1,白骨雏龙,104000101,<color=#3D53AE>遗言</color>：抽1张白骨龙,baiguchulong,baiguchulong_s,4,\"4,10\",,,3,1,2,1,1,,,2,,,,,,嘎吱嘎吱嘎吱（翻译：别欺负我，我头上有龙。）\r\r\n,1040002,1,白骨龙,104000201,<color=#3D53AE>遗言</color>：抽1张白骨龙灵,baigulong,baigulong_s,4,\"4,10\",,,4,2,3,2,1,,,2,,,,,,嘎吱——嘎吱——（翻译：大的要来了。）\r\r\n,1040003,1,白骨龙灵,104000301,若场上的友方<color=#3D53AE>龙</color>≥2，本牌费用为0,baigulongling,baigulongling_s,4,\"4,10\",,,5,3,4,3,1,,,,,,,,,龙，我罩的，懂？\r\r\n,1040004,1,白眼青龙,104000401,本牌费用=你的牌组中剩余牌的数量,baiyanqinglong,baiyanqinglong_s,4,4,,,4,99,30,25,1,,,,,,,,,无论在哪儿他都贵得离谱。\r\r\n,104000401,1,白眼青龙,104000401,本牌费用=你的牌组中剩余牌的数量,baiyanqinglong,baiyanqinglong_s,4,4,,,4,99,30,25,,,,101,,,,,,无论在哪儿他都贵得离谱。\r\r\n,104000402,1,白眼青龙,104000401,本牌费用=你的牌组中剩余牌的数量,baiyanqinglong,baiyanqinglong_s,4,4,,,4,99,30,25,,,,101,,,,,,无论在哪儿他都贵得离谱。\r\r\n,104000403,1,白眼青龙,104000401,本牌费用=你的牌组中剩余牌的数量,baiyanqinglong,baiyanqinglong_s,4,4,,,4,99,30,25,,,,101,,,,,,无论在哪儿他都贵得离谱。\r\r\n,1040005,1,噬魂之龙,104000501,<color=#3D53AE>唯一</color>。<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：友方墓地每有1只<color=#3D53AE>龙</color>，则造成1点伤害，随机分配到所有敌人身上,shihunzhilong,shihunzhilong_s,4,\"4,10\",,,5,3,5,3,1,,,\"1,4\",,,,,,吞噬你的灵魂。\r\r\n,104000501,1,噬魂之龙,104000501,<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：友方墓地每有1只<color=#3D53AE>龙</color>，则造成1点伤害，随机分配到所有敌人身上,shihunzhilong,shihunzhilong_s,4,4,,,5,3,5,3,,,,\"1,101\",,,,,,吞噬你的灵魂。\r\r\n,1040006,1,守护之龙,5,<color=#3D53AE>嘲讽</color>,shouhuzhilong,shouhuzhilong_s,4,4,,,4,3,2,12,1,,,13,,,,,,五个字教你嘲讽贾巴沃克：绷急典孝乐。\r\r\n,1040007,1,赐福者,104000701,<color=#3D53AE>唯一</color>。<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：若场上有其他友方<color=#3D53AE>龙</color>，本随从获得<color=#3D53AE>无敌</color>并+2攻击,cifuzhe,cifuzhe_s,4,4,,,5,2,4,3,1,,,\"4,1,12\",,zhanchanglong,+1,,,尊重，理解，祝福，最后立于不败之地。\r\r\n,1040008,1,尖刺之龙,\"104000801,7\",<color=#3D53AE>穿透</color>。若场上有其他友方<color=#3D53AE>龙</color>，本随从+3攻击,jiancizhilong,jiancizhilong_s,4,4,,,5,3,6,4,1,,,19,,,,,,\"冒险家协会报酬最高的挑战任务，名称：驯服刺头。\r\n任务要求：拔下尖刺之龙双翼上最坚硬的两根骨刺。\r\n报酬：100,000,000,000金币。\"\r\r\n,1040009,1,炎翼龙,104000901,友方回合结束时，对敌方英雄造成2点伤害,yanyilong,yanyilong_s,4,4,,,3,3,4,4,1,,,,,,,,,黯淡之火，混沌之力，死亡之翼。\r\r\n,2000116,2,王权幻像,200011601,若你的<color=#3D53AE>恶魔暴君弥达斯</color>已死亡，则召唤1个<color=#3D53AE>恶魔暴君弥达斯</color>,wangquanhuanxiang,,,,2,2,5,3,,,2,,,,,,,,,伊缇露丝，我亲爱的小鸟……\r\r\n,1040011,1,飞龙幼崽,104001101,<color=#3D53AE>遗言</color>：对敌方英雄造成1点伤害,feilongyouzai,feilongyouzai_s,4,4,,,2,0,1,1,1,,,2,,,,,,把蛋壳还给我！\r\r\n,1040012,1,烈焰雏龙,104001201,<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：对敌方英雄造成2点伤害,lieyanchulong,lieyanchulong_s,4,4,,,1,2,3,3,1,,,1,,,,,,雏龙吐火——不知轻重。\r\r\n,1040013,1,淘气小龙,,,qiangxifeilong,qiangxifeilong_s,4,4,,,1,1,3,2,1,,,,,,,,,\r\r\n,104001301,1,淘气小龙,,,qiangxifeilong,qiangxifeilong_s,4,4,,,1,1,3,2,,,,101,,,,,,\r\r\n,1040014,1,龙语者,104001401,<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：获得1张雏龙,longyuzhe,longyuzhe_s,4,4,,,2,2,3,2,1,,,1,,,,,,且听龙吟。\r\r\n,104001401,1,龙语者,,,longyuzhe,longyuzhe_s,4,4,,,1,1,3,2,,,,101,,,,,,且听龙吟。\r\r\n,1040015,1,保护之龙,,,baohuzhilong,baohuzhilong_s,4,4,,,1,2,3,4,1,,,,,,,,,\"禁止猎杀未成年幼龙，违者依法严惩。\r\n（歪歪扭扭的字迹：你也不想被流放到龙巢去吧？）\"\r\r\n,104001501,1,保护之龙,,,baohuzhilong,baohuzhilong_s,4,4,,,1,2,3,4,,,,101,,,,,,\"禁止猎杀未成年幼龙，违者依法严惩。\r\n（歪歪扭扭的字迹：你也不想被流放到龙巢去吧？）\"\r\r\n,1020003,1,魔力引导者,102000301,<color=#3D53AE>遗言</color>：你使用的下1张<color=#B92661>寒霜教会</color>费用-2,moliyindaozhe,moliyindaozhe_s,2,7,6,6,4,1,2,2,5,,,2,,,,,,唯心主义者的免费，只需两点生命的代价。\r\r\n,1030010,1,天才,\"103001001,103001002\",<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：弃掉手牌中的1张<color=#B92661>冰能魔晶</color>，获得2张<color=#3D53AE>巫师</color>随从,tiancai,tiancai_s,3,5,,,3,1,2,3,5,,,1,,shoupaibingjing,+1,,,天才第一步，咒语先背熟。\r\r\n,1040010,1,驯龙师,104001001,<color=#3D53AE>遗言</color>：从你的手牌中召唤1个费用≤3的<color=#3D53AE>龙</color>,xunlongshi,xunlongshi_s,4,5,,,4,2,3,2,4,,,2,,,,,,呼唤小狗的拟声词对小龙无效。\r\r\n,1040016,1,掌灯者,104001601,<color=#3D53AE>限二</color>。每使用1张<color=#B92661>攻击牌</color>或<color=#B92661>特殊攻击牌</color>，本随从获得+2+2,zhangdengzhe,zhangdengzhe_s,4,5,,\"8,-1|9,-1\",4,2,1,1,2,,,28,,,,,,他从太阳西沉熄那一刻开始点燃灯芯，巡视王城，直至黎明将至，夜夜亦然。\r\r\n,1050001,1,疯狂科学家,105000101,<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：本回合你使用的下2张<color=#B92661>发条梦境</color>牌费用-3,fengkuangkexuejia,fengkuangkexuejia_s,5,3,3,3,5,2,2,2,1,,,1,,,,,,尽管王国已经严令禁止学者们研究世界发展的规律，但她的好奇心无法被律法束缚。\r\r\n,105000101,1,疯狂科学家,105000101,<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：本回合你使用的下2张<color=#B92661>发条梦境</color>牌费用-3,fengkuangkexuejia,fengkuangkexuejia_s,5,3,3,3,5,2,2,2,,,,\"1,101\",,,,,,尽管王国已经严令禁止学者们研究世界发展的规律，但她的好奇心无法被律法束缚。\r\r\n,1050002,1,炸药飞艇,\"105000201,105000202\",<color=#3D53AE>遗言</color>：若你的手牌中有<color=#B92661>发条梦境</color>牌，则对所有敌方随从造成4点伤害,zhayaofeiting,zhayaofeiting_s,5,3,3,3,5,3,4,4,1,,,2,,,,,,设定新航程，操纵杆启动，方位已设定，准备进行轰炸。\r\r\n,105000201,1,炸药飞艇,\"105000201,105000202\",<color=#3D53AE>遗言</color>：若你的手牌中有<color=#B92661>发条梦境</color>牌，则对所有敌方随从造成4点伤害,zhayaofeiting,zhayaofeiting_s,5,3,3,3,5,3,4,4,,,,\"2,101\",,,,,,设定新航程，操纵杆启动，方位已设定，准备进行轰炸。\r\r\n,1050003,1,强袭装甲,105000301,<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：使1个敌方随从变为1/1,qiangxizhuangjia,qiangxizhuangjia_s,5,3,3,3,5,3,4,4,1,3,,1,,,,,,武力威慑！\r\r\n,105000301,1,强袭装甲,105000301,<color=#3D53AE>入场</color>：使1个敌方随从变为1/1,qiangxizhuangjia,qiangxizhuangjia_s,5,3,3,3,5,3,4,4,,3,,\"1,101\",,,,,,武力威慑！\r\r\n,1050004,1,机械玛丽,105000401,场上所有<color=#3D53AE>机械</color>随从+1+1,jixiemali,jixiemali_s,5,3,,,2,2,2,2,1,,,,,,,,,玛丽精心照顾着每一个她眼里的“孩子”。\r\r[... 70518 more characters truncated]"}],"details":{"persistedDetailsTruncated":true,"originalDetailsBytesAtLeast":8193,"originalDetailKeys":["status","exitCode","durationMs","aggregated","cwd"],"status":"completed","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace","exitCode":0},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779780897413}}
{"type":"message","id":"2d568ee8","parentId":"94467b8b","timestamp":"2026-05-26T07:35:07.022Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a very comprehensive understanding of the Luban table system. Let me summarize:\n\n**Luban Config Structure (SoloConfig):**\n\n1. **Schema Definition:**\n   - `luban.conf` - Main config file\n   - `Defines/builtin.xml` - Built-in types (vector2, vector3, vector4)\n   - `Datas/__tables__.xlsx` - Table definitions (what tables exist, their xlsx file, mode, group)\n   - `Datas/__beans__.xlsx` - Bean/complex type definitions\n   - `Datas/__enums__.xlsx` - Enum type definitions\n\n2. **Table Data Files (in Datas/):**\n   - Each xlsx file corresponds to a table (e.g., `Card.xlsx`, `Buff.xlsx`, `Common.xlsx`)\n   - The schema is read from the Excel file itself (`read_schema_from_file=TRUE`)\n\n3. **Excel File Format:**\n   - Row 1 (header): `##var` (field name), `##type` (data type), `##group` (c/s/e), then description/data\n   - Row 2: Comment/description row (optional)\n   - Row 3+: Data rows\n\n4. **Field Types:**\n   - Basic: `int`, `float`, `long`, `string`, `bool`\n   - Collections: `(list#sep=,),int`, `(set#sep=,),int`, `(list#sep=|),string`\n   - Complex beans: Referenced by bean name\n   \n5. **Key-Value Tables** (like `Common.xlsx`): Key-value pairs where each row is a setting\n   - Structure: `##column#var`, `##type`, `##group`, description, default_value\n\n6. **List Tables** (like `Card.xlsx`): Multiple rows of data\n   - Structure: `##var` (field names like `id`, `type`, `name`, etc.), `##type`, `##group`, comment, actual data\n\nThe task \"给表格添加字段\" (add fields to tables) means adding a new column/field to an existing Excel data table and potentially updating related schema.\n\nI need to create a skill for this. Let me read the skill-creator skill first.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"好，我对 SoloConfig 的 Luban 配置系统已经有了完整了解！让我先读一下 skill-creator 的流程。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_cs3OLkxloD91603W4RaC8798","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/AppData/Roaming/npm/node_modules/openclaw/skills/skill-creator/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":51622,"output":590,"cacheRead":48256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":100468,"cost":{"input":0.00722708,"output":0.0001652,"cacheRead":0.001351168,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.008743448000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779780897415,"responseId":"b4c19603-ad2d-4cce-ba91-09f0e8c0e93b"}}
{"type":"message","id":"41371dab","parentId":"2d568ee8","timestamp":"2026-05-26T07:35:07.047Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_cs3OLkxloD91603W4RaC8798","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: skill-creator\ndescription: Create, edit, improve, tidy, review, audit, or restructure AgentSkills and SKILL.md files.\n---\n\n# Skill Creator\n\nThis skill provides guidance for creating effective skills.\n\n## About Skills\n\nSkills are modular, self-contained packages that extend Codex's capabilities by providing\nspecialized knowledge, workflows, and tools. Think of them as \"onboarding guides\" for specific\ndomains or tasks—they transform Codex from a general-purpose agent into a specialized agent\nequipped with procedural knowledge that no model can fully possess.\n\n### What Skills Provide\n\n1. Specialized workflows - Multi-step procedures for specific domains\n2. Tool integrations - Instructions for working with specific file formats or APIs\n3. Domain expertise - Company-specific knowledge, schemas, business logic\n4. Bundled resources - Scripts, references, and assets for complex and repetitive tasks\n\n## Core Principles\n\n### Concise is Key\n\nThe context window is a public good. Skills share the context window with everything else Codex needs: system prompt, conversation history, other Skills' metadata, and the actual user request.\n\n**Default assumption: Codex is already very smart.** Only add context Codex doesn't already have. Challenge each piece of information: \"Does Codex really need this explanation?\" and \"Does this paragraph justify its token cost?\"\n\nPrefer concise examples over verbose explanations.\n\n### Set Appropriate Degrees of Freedom\n\nMatch the level of specificity to the task's fragility and variability:\n\n**High freedom (text-based instructions)**: Use when multiple approaches are valid, decisions depend on context, or heuristics guide the approach.\n\n**Medium freedom (pseudocode or scripts with parameters)**: Use when a preferred pattern exists, some variation is acceptable, or configuration affects behavior.\n\n**Low freedom (specific scripts, few parameters)**: Use when operations are fragile and error-prone, consistency is critical, or a specific sequence must be followed.\n\nThink of Codex as exploring a path: a narrow bridge with cliffs needs specific guardrails (low freedom), while an open field allows many routes (high freedom).\n\n### Anatomy of a Skill\n\nEvery skill consists of a required SKILL.md file and optional bundled resources:\n\n```\nskill-name/\n├── SKILL.md (required)\n│   ├── YAML frontmatter metadata (required)\n│   │   ├── name: (required)\n│   │   └── description: (required)\n│   └── Markdown instructions (required)\n└── Bundled Resources (optional)\n    ├── scripts/          - Executable code (Python/Bash/etc.)\n    ├── references/       - Documentation intended to be loaded into context as needed\n    └── assets/           - Files used in output (templates, icons, fonts, etc.)\n```\n\n#### SKILL.md (required)\n\nEvery SKILL.md consists of:\n\n- **Frontmatter** (YAML): Contains `name` and `description` fields. These are the only fields that Codex reads to determine when the skill gets used, thus it is very important to be clear and comprehensive in describing what the skill is, and when it should be used.\n- **Body** (Markdown): Instructions and guidance for using the skill. Only loaded AFTER the skill triggers (if at all).\n\n#### Bundled Resources (optional)\n\n##### Scripts (`scripts/`)\n\nExecutable code (Python/Bash/etc.) for tasks that require deterministic reliability or are repeatedly rewritten.\n\n- **When to include**: When the same code is being rewritten repeatedly or deterministic reliability is needed\n- **Example**: `scripts/rotate_pdf.py` for PDF rotation tasks\n- **Benefits**: Token efficient, deterministic, may be executed without loading into context\n- **Note**: Scripts may still need to be read by Codex for patching or environment-specific adjustments\n\n##### References (`references/`)\n\nDocumentation and reference material intended to be loaded as needed into context to inform Codex's process and thinking.\n\n- **When to include**: For documentation that Codex should reference while working\n- **Examples**: `references/finance.md` for financial schemas, `references/mnda.md` for company NDA template, `references/policies.md` for company policies, `references/api_docs.md` for API specifications\n- **Use cases**: Database schemas, API documentation, domain knowledge, company policies, detailed workflow guides\n- **Benefits**: Keeps SKILL.md lean, loaded only when Codex determines it's needed\n- **Best practice**: If files are large (>10k words), include grep search patterns in SKILL.md\n- **Avoid duplication**: Information should live in either SKILL.md or references files, not both. Prefer references files for detailed information unless it's truly core to the skill—this keeps SKILL.md lean while making information discoverable without hogging the context window. Keep only essential procedural instructions and workflow guidance in SKILL.md; move detailed reference material, schemas, and examples to references files.\n\n##### Assets (`assets/`)\n\nFiles not intended to be loaded into context, but rather used within the output Codex produces.\n\n- **When to include**: When the skill needs files that will be used in the final output\n- **Examples**: `assets/logo.png` for brand assets, `assets/slides.pptx` for PowerPoint templates, `assets/frontend-template/` for HTML/React boilerplate, `assets/font.ttf` for typography\n- **Use cases**: Templates, images, icons, boilerplate code, fonts, sample documents that get copied or modified\n- **Benefits**: Separates output resources from documentation, enables Codex to use files without loading them into context\n\n#### What to Not Include in a Skill\n\nA skill should only contain essential files that directly support its functionality. Do NOT create extraneous documentation or auxiliary files, including:\n\n- README.md\n- INSTALLATION_GUIDE.md\n- QUICK_REFERENCE.md\n- CHANGELOG.md\n- etc.\n\nThe skill should only contain the information needed for an AI agent to do the job at hand. It should not contain auxiliary context about the process that went into creating it, setup and testing procedures, user-facing documentation, etc. Creating additional documentation files just adds clutter and confusion.\n\n### Progressive Disclosure Design Principle\n\nSkills use a three-level loading system to manage context efficiently:\n\n1. **Metadata (name + description)** - Always in context (~100 words)\n2. **SKILL.md body** - When skill triggers (<5k words)\n3. **Bundled resources** - As needed by Codex (Unlimited because scripts can be executed without reading into context window)\n\n#### Progressive Disclosure Patterns\n\nKeep SKILL.md body to the essentials and under 500 lines to minimize context bloat. Split content into separate files when approaching this limit. When splitting out content into other files, it is very important to reference them from SKILL.md and describe clearly when to read them, to ensure the reader of the skill knows they exist and when to use them.\n\n**Key principle:** When a skill supports multiple variations, frameworks, or options, keep only the core workflow and selection guidance in SKILL.md. Move variant-specific details (patterns, examples, configuration) into separate reference files.\n\n**Pattern 1: High-level guide with references**\n\n```markdown\n# PDF Processing\n\n## Quick start\n\nExtract text with pdfplumber:\n[code example]\n\n## Advanced features\n\n- **Form filling**: See [FORMS.md](FORMS.md) for complete guide\n- **API reference**: See [REFERENCE.md](REFERENCE.md) for all methods\n- **Examples**: See [EXAMPLES.md](EXAMPLES.md) for common patterns\n```\n\nCodex loads FORMS.md, REFERENCE.md, or EXAMPLES.md only when needed.\n\n**Pattern 2: Domain-specific organization**\n\nFor Skills with multiple domains, organize content by domain to avoid loading irrelevant context:\n\n```\nbigquery-skill/\n├── SKILL.md (overview and navigation)\n└── reference/\n    ├── finance.md (revenue, billing metrics)\n    ├── sales.md (opportunities, pipeline)\n    ├── product.md (API usage, features)\n    └── marketing.md (campaigns, attribution)\n```\n\nWhen a user asks about sales metrics, Codex only reads sales.md.\n\nSimilarly, for skills supporting multiple frameworks or variants, organize by variant:\n\n```\ncloud-deploy/\n├── SKILL.md (workflow + provider selection)\n└── references/\n    ├── aws.md (AWS deployment patterns)\n    ├── gcp.md (GCP deployment patterns)\n    └── azure.md (Azure deployment patterns)\n```\n\nWhen the user chooses AWS, Codex only reads aws.md.\n\n**Pattern 3: Conditional details**\n\nShow basic content, link to advanced content:\n\n```markdown\n# DOCX Processing\n\n## Creating documents\n\nUse docx-js for new documents. See [DOCX-JS.md](DOCX-JS.md).\n\n## Editing documents\n\nFor simple edits, modify the XML directly.\n\n**For tracked changes**: See [REDLINING.md](REDLINING.md)\n**For OOXML details**: See [OOXML.md](OOXML.md)\n```\n\nCodex reads REDLINING.md or OOXML.md only when the user needs those features.\n\n**Important guidelines:**\n\n- **Avoid deeply nested references** - Keep references one level deep from SKILL.md. All reference files should link directly from SKILL.md.\n- **Structure longer reference files** - For files longer than 100 lines, include a table of contents at the top so Codex can see the full scope when previewing.\n\n## Skill Creation Process\n\nSkill creation involves these steps:\n\n1. Understand the skill with concrete examples\n2. Plan reusable skill contents (scripts, references, assets)\n3. Initialize the skill (run init_skill.py)\n4. Edit the skill (implement resources and write SKILL.md)\n5. Package the skill (run package_skill.py)\n6. Iterate based on real usage\n\nFollow these steps in order, skipping only if there is a clear reason why they are not applicable.\n\n### Skill Naming\n\n- Use lowercase letters, digits, and hyphens only; normalize user-provided titles to hyphen-case (e.g., \"Plan Mode\" -> `plan-mode`).\n- When generating names, generate a name under 64 characters (letters, digits, hyphens).\n- Prefer short, verb-led phrases that describe the action.\n- Namespace by tool when it improves clarity or triggering (e.g., `gh-address-comments`, `linear-address-issue`).\n- Name the skill folder exactly after the skill name.\n\n### Step 1: Understanding the Skill with Concrete Examples\n\nSkip this step only when the skill's usage patterns are already clearly understood. It remains valuable even when working with an existing skill.\n\nTo create an effective skill, clearly understand concrete examples of how the skill will be used. This understanding can come from either direct user examples or generated examples that are validated with user feedback.\n\nFor example, when building an image-editor skill, relevant questions include:\n\n- \"What functionality should the image-editor skill support? Editing, rotating, anything else?\"\n- \"Can you give some examples of how this skill would be used?\"\n- \"I can imagine users asking for things like 'Remove the red-eye from this image' or 'Rotate this image'. Are there other ways you imagine this skill being used?\"\n- \"What would a user say that should trigger this skill?\"\n\nTo avoid overwhelming users, avoid asking too many questions in a single message. Start with the most important questions and follow up as needed for better effectiveness.\n\nConclude this step when there is a clear sense of the functionality the skill should support.\n\n### Step 2: Planning the Reusable Skill Contents\n\nTo turn concrete examples into an effective skill, analyze each example by:\n\n1. Considering how to execute on the example from scratch\n2. Identifying what scripts, references, and assets would be helpful when executing these workflows repeatedly\n\nExample: When building a `pdf-editor` skill to handle queries like \"Help me rotate this PDF,\" the analysis shows:\n\n1. Rotating a PDF requires re-writing the same code each time\n2. A `scripts/rotate_pdf.py` script would be helpful to store in the skill\n\n\n⚠️ [... middle content omitted — showing head and tail ...]\n\n\n#### Learn Proven Design Patterns\n\nConsult these helpful guides based on your skill's needs:\n\n- **Multi-step processes**: See references/workflows.md for sequential workflows and conditional logic\n- **Specific output formats or quality standards**: See references/output-patterns.md for template and example patterns\n\nThese files contain established best practices for effective skill design.\n\n#### Start with Reusable Skill Contents\n\nTo begin implementation, start with the reusable resources identified above: `scripts/`, `references/`, and `assets/` files. Note that this step may require user input. For example, when implementing a `brand-guidelines` skill, the user may need to provide brand assets or templates to store in `assets/`, or documentation to store in `references/`.\n\nAdded scripts must be tested by actually running them to ensure there are no bugs and that the output matches what is expected. If there are many similar scripts, only a representative sample needs to be tested to ensure confidence that they all work while balancing time to completion.\n\nIf you used `--examples`, delete any placeholder files that are not needed for the skill. Only create resource directories that are actually required.\n\n#### Update SKILL.md\n\n**Writing Guidelines:** Always use imperative/infinitive form.\n\n##### Frontmatter\n\nWrite the YAML frontmatter with `name` and `description`:\n\n- `name`: The skill name\n- `description`: This is the primary triggering mechanism for your skill, and helps Codex understand when to use the skill.\n  - Include both what the Skill does and specific triggers/contexts for when to use it.\n  - Include all \"when to use\" information here - Not in the body. The body is only loaded after triggering, so \"When to Use This Skill\" sections in the body are not helpful to Codex.\n  - Example description for a `docx` skill: \"Comprehensive document creation, editing, and analysis with support for tracked changes, comments, formatting preservation, and text extraction. Use when Codex needs to work with professional documents (.docx files) for: (1) Creating new documents, (2) Modifying or editing content, (3) Working with tracked changes, (4) Adding comments, or any other document tasks\"\n\nDo not include any other fields in YAML frontmatter.\n\n##### Body\n\nWrite instructions for using the skill and its bundled resources.\n\n### Step 5: Packaging a Skill\n\nOnce development of the skill is complete, it must be packaged into a distributable .skill file that gets shared with the user. The packaging process automatically validates the skill first to ensure it meets all requirements:\n\n```bash\nscripts/package_skill.py <path/to/skill-folder>\n```\n\nOptional output directory specification:\n\n```bash\nscripts/package_skill.py <path/to/skill-folder> ./dist\n```\n\nThe packaging script will:\n\n1. **Validate** the skill automatically, checking:\n   - YAML frontmatter format and required fields\n   - Skill naming conventions and directory structure\n   - Description completeness and quality\n   - File organization and resource references\n\n2. **Package** the skill if validation passes, creating a .skill file named after the skill (e.g., `my-skill.skill`) that includes all files and maintains the proper directory structure for distribution. The .skill file is a zip file with a .skill extension.\n\n   Security restriction: symlinks are rejected and packaging fails when any symlink is present.\n\nIf validation fails, the script will report the errors and exit without creating a package. Fix any validation errors and run the packaging command again.\n\n### Step 6: Iterate\n\nAfter testing the skill, users may request improvements. Often this happens right after using the skill, with fresh context of how the skill performed.\n\n**Iteration workflow:**\n\n1. Use the skill on real tasks\n2. Notice struggles or inefficiencies\n3. Identify how SKILL.md or bundled resources should be updated\n4. Implement changes and test again\n[... 2457 more characters truncated]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1779780907047}}
{"type":"message","id":"0e2fd312","parentId":"41371dab","timestamp":"2026-05-26T07:35:19.818Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, the skill-creator skill provides guidance. Since this is a new private/custom skill (not public), I don't need to use init_skill.py or package it into .skill format. I'll just create the skill directory and SKILL.md directly in the plugin-skills folder where other skills live.\n\nLet me now design the skill:\n\n**Skill Name:** `solo-config-field` (or something similar)\n\n**What it does:** Add fields to Luban config tables in the SoloConfig submodule.\n\n**Context:**\n- SoloConfig is at `E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\config\\SoloConfig`\n- It uses Luban as the config tool\n- Tables are defined in `Datas/__tables__.xlsx`\n- Beans are defined in `Datas/__beans__.xlsx`\n- Enums are defined in `Datas/__enums__.xlsx`\n- Data files are xlsx files in `Datas/` directory\n- Schema is read from Excel files (header rows)\n- Some tables use key-value format (like Common.xlsx), others use list format (like Card.xlsx)\n\n**Workflow for adding a field:**\n1. Identify the table (xlsx file) to modify\n2. Open the xlsx file\n3. Add a new column with the field name, type, group, and default values\n4. Update related Lua/C# code if needed\n5. Run Luban to generate new code\n\nWait, I need to consider what \"给表格添加字段\" actually means in practical terms. Let me think about the full workflow:\n\n1. User says \"给xxx表加一个yyy字段，类型是zzz\"\n2. I need to:\n   a. Find the right xlsx file in `Datas/`\n   b. Add the field as a new column\n   c. If it's a bean/struct type, update `__beans__.xlsx`\n   d. If new enum values are needed, update `__enums__.xlsx`\n   e. Run Luban to regenerate code\n   f. Commit the changes\n\nFor this, I need to:\n- Be able to read/write xlsx files (need openpyxl or xlsx npm package)\n- Understand the Luban Excel format\n\nLet me check what tools are available for xlsx manipulation.\n\nActually, let me think about this more practically. The skill should handle:\n\n1. **Add column to list-type table** (most common case): \n   - Open xlsx, add new column header with `##var`/`##type`/`##group` rows\n   - Fill in default values for all existing rows\n   \n2. **Add key-value to Common.xlsx** (key-value config):\n   - Add new row with name, type, description, default value\n\n3. **Update __tables__.xlsx** (if adding entirely new table):\n   - Add new row referencing the table\n\n4. **Update __beans__.xlsx** (if adding new bean type):\n   - Add new bean definition\n\nLet me check checkered or tp-server directories for more context on how the pipeline works (code generation, etc.).","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"让我再看看 checker 和 tp-server 目录了解代码生成流程。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_DJ5gQbvdkit6Dcd7yYgi3244","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cmd /c \"cd /d E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\config\\SoloConfig && dir /B checker && echo --- && dir /B xlsx2json\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":4037,"output":782,"cacheRead":100352,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":105171,"cost":{"input":0.0005651800000000001,"output":0.00021896,"cacheRead":0.002809856,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003593996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779780907049,"responseId":"1ac09a05-9dc6-4677-86d3-2f9221eca3ad"}}
