{"type":"message","id":"2e82bfe1","parentId":"6e427ce2","timestamp":"2026-05-26T07:37:20.200Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so `readFile` is `undefined` because the xlsx package was just installed and the API has changed. The function is `read` not `readFile`. Let me check: `X.read` and `X.write` exist, and `X.utils` exists. So I need to use:\n\n- `X.read(data, { type: 'buffer' })` instead of `X.readFile(path)`\n- `X.write(wb, { type: 'buffer', bookType: 'xlsx' })` instead of `X.writeFile(path)`\n\nOr... wait, let me check the version more carefully.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_s1kvSMrlDz2yURhb3FNS8789","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\_test_xlsx.mjs","content":"import { readFileSync, writeFileSync } from 'fs';\nimport * as X from 'xlsx';\nconsole.log('version:', X.version);\nconsole.log('readFile:', typeof X.readFile);\nconsole.log('writeFile:', typeof X.writeFile);\nconsole.log('read:', typeof X.read);\nconsole.log('write:', typeof X.write);\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":158,"output":279,"cacheRead":119680,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":120117,"cost":{"input":0.00002212,"output":0.00007812,"cacheRead":0.00335104,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00345128}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779781036267,"responseId":"8cdb17c6-0965-4d95-a161-0e2f2ed80c5c"}}
