{"type":"message","id":"b2c34d53","parentId":"9e6c5755","timestamp":"2026-05-26T07:54:04.669Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The xlsx2csv output for the first row shows the columns. Let me count the columns in the first row by looking at the CSV.\n\nActually, the xlsx2csv output I already have shows the ##var row:\n```\n##var,id,HeroId,name,down_desc,SkinIcon,Skin_FX,twoPlayerIcon,SkinSpineAni,inTimeline,changeTimeline,heroBorderFX,cardFX,head_icon,deck_icon,replace_eft_change,replace_eft_death,replace_voice_begin,replace_voice_in,replace_voice_change,replace_voice_death,replace_voice_win,replace_voice_game\n```\n\nThat's 23 fields. The new field (Offset) is at column 24, which wouldn't show in CSV because no data row has a value for it and xlsx2csv might not include trailing empty columns. Let me check by using the script to read the file instead.\n\nActually, let me directly verify using node.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_56rt2NeQtfGdGzyw3Vgu2419","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"node -e \"import * as X from 'xlsx'; import {readFileSync} from 'fs'; const wb = X.read(readFileSync('E:/Solo/nightoffullmoon/client/config/SoloConfig/Datas/HeroSkin.xlsx'),{type:'buffer'}); const ws=wb.Sheets[wb.SheetNames[0]]; const rows=X.utils.sheet_to_json(ws,{header:1}); const last=rows[0].filter(c=>c!==undefined&&String(c).trim()!=='').pop(); console.log('Last header:',last); console.log('Total cols:', rows[0].length); console.log('Row 2 cols:', rows[1].length);\"","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":53,"output":423,"cacheRead":108928,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":109404,"cost":{"input":0.00000742,"output":0.00011844000000000001,"cacheRead":0.003049984,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003175844}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779782039052,"responseId":"89e2c036-87bd-436d-b667-664f59c0fd23"}}
