{"type":"message","id":"e2bd6b0c","parentId":"c1c98491","timestamp":"2026-05-26T07:54:11.403Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The xlsx file still has 23 columns! The write didn't actually add the field column to the file. Looking at my `addToListTable` function, it modifies the `ws` object by adding cells, but it doesn't actually increase the `!ref` range of the worksheet. The `!ref` property (like `A1:W5`) determines what part of the sheet is considered \"in use\". When I add a cell outside the current range, I need to update the `!ref` property.\n\nLet me check - `XLSX.utils.encode_cell` creates the cell address like `X24`. When I set `ws[cell] = ...`, the cell gets added to the worksheet, but the `!ref` doesn't update automatically. When `XLSX.write` is called, it uses `!ref` to determine what to write.\n\nI need to update the `!ref` after adding cells. Let me fix the script.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"找到了——写入后没更新 `!ref` 范围，导致新列被截掉了。修一下。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_GwRnTgj1g2YuGGmD0RhF6917","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\plugin-skills\\solo-config-field\\scripts\\add_field.mjs","edits":[{"oldText":"  // Update column widths\n  if (ws['!cols']) {\n    ws['!cols'].push({ wch: Math.max(fieldName.length * 2, 10) });\n  }\n\n  console.log(`✅ Added field \"${fieldName}\" (${fieldType}) at column index ${insertCol + 1}`);\n  return true;","newText":"  // Update !ref range to include the new column\n  if (ws['!ref']) {\n    const ref = XLSX.utils.decode_range(ws['!ref']);\n    if (insertCol > ref.e.c) {\n      ref.e.c = insertCol;\n      ws['!ref'] = XLSX.utils.encode_range(ref);\n    }\n  }\n\n  console.log(`✅ Added field \"${fieldName}\" (${fieldType}) at column index ${insertCol + 1}`);\n  return true;"}]}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":125,"output":523,"cacheRead":109312,"cacheWrit