{"type":"message","id":"cf025bea","parentId":"2c987928","timestamp":"2026-05-26T09:31:47.795Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, I found several Unity MCP packages. The key ones are:\n\n1. **`unity-mcp`** (v1.1.0) - by artmann, simple MCP server for Unity\n2. **`anklebreaker-unity-mcp`** (v2.29.0) - by anklebreaker-studio, multi-agent MCP server for Unity Editor designed for Claude Cowork\n3. **`@iflow-mcp/unity-mcp-server`** (v3.1.1) - simple HTTP-based Unity Editor integration\n4. **`@akiojin/unity-mcp-server`** (v5.5.2) - MCP server and Unity Editor bridge\n5. **`unity-mcp-bridge`** (v0.6.4) - MCP Bridge for Unity Editor\n\nThe most popular one seems to be `anklebreaker-unity-mcp` (v2.29.0, latest) which is designed for Claude Cowork. But the user's Unity version is 2020.3.49f1 which is quite old. Most MCP solutions use UDP/HTTP to communicate with the Unity Editor, and they usually require a Unity package (`.unitypackage`) to be installed in the project.\n\nFor Unity 2020.3.49f1 compatibility, I need to check what versions of Unity these MCP packages support. The `anklebreaker-unity-mcp` is the most actively maintained one. Let me look at their details to find the right download.\n\nActually, the user said \"去unity官方下载\" - go to Unity official to download. But Unity MCP is NOT an official Unity product - it's a community tool. The user might not know the exact name. Let me look at the `anklebreaker-unity-mcp` package more closely since it seems to be the most popular one.\n\nLet me fetch the details of these packages.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_Asb3v76yIapux5QI0xTE8381","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cmd /c \"npm view unity-mcp description version 2>NUL && echo --- && npm view anklebreaker-unity-mcp description version 2>NUL\"","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":1907,"output":498,"cacheRead":1