{"type":"message","id":"d39318d1","parentId":"6610cf98","timestamp":"2026-05-26T09:32:38.081Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The npm package only contains the server-side code (the MCP server that runs on Node.js). The Unity side plugin is a separate thing installed via UPM git URL. Let me provide the user with:\n\n1. The downloaded npm package (already done)\n2. Instructions for both parts - the npm server and the Unity plugin\n\nLet me also check if the `unity-mcp-bridge` package might have a simpler setup or be more compatible.\n\nActually, I already have the right solution. Let me inform the user about what I've found and downloaded, and how to set it up.\n\nActually, let me also check the other simple `unity-mcp` package in case it supports Unity 2020 as well.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_Kh1hi5TdriWlyOnhsX6X7688","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cmd /c \"npm view unity-mcp readme 2>NUL\"","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":91,"output":222,"cacheRead":139136,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":139449,"cost":{"input":0.000012740000000000002,"output":0.00006216,"cacheRead":0.0038958079999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003970708}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779787953471,"responseId":"46a51259-a30a-459d-be54-b83c42991df1"}}
{"type":"message","id":"8b1adf74","parentId":"d39318d1","timestamp":"2026-05-26T09:32:39.065Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_Kh1hi5TdriWlyOnhsX6X7688","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Unity MCP Server\n\nMCP server to connect Claude with Unity projects. Built using the [Model Context Protocol SDK](https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/typescript-sdk).\n\n## Features\n- List all Unity projects \n- Get detailed project information\n- Access project structure and files\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Run this project locally\nRun this project locally by cloning this repo\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/your-username/unity-mcp.git\ncd unity-mcp\nbun install\n```\n\nAdd this tool as an MCP server in Claude.\n\nOn MacOS: `~/Library/Application\\ Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json`  \nOn Windows: `%APPDATA%/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"mcpServers\": {\n    \"unity\": {\n      \"command\": \"bun\",\n      \"args\": [\"run\", \"C:\\\\Users\\\\Artga\\\\Code\\\\unity-mcp\\\\src\\\\index.ts\"]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Requirements\n- Unity with projects configured\n- Bun runtime\n\n### Troubleshooting\nPlease open an issue if you can't get this MCP working. Here are some tips:\n1. Make sure Unity is installed and you have some projects configured\n2. Check that the unity-mcp server can access the projects-v1.json file\n3. Ensure you have proper permissions for the Unity project directories\n\nThis MCP will emit logs to stderr as specified in the MCP spec. On Mac the Claude Desktop app should emit these logs\nto `~/Library/Logs/Claude`. \nOn other platforms [you can find logs here](https://modelcontextprotocol.io/quickstart/user#getting-logs-from-claude-for-desktop).\n\n## Development\n\n### Setup\n```bash\n# Install dependencies\nbun install\n\n# Run the project\nbun run src/index.ts\n\n# Type check\nbun run typecheck\n\n# Format code\nbun run format\n```\n\n### Debugging\n\nSince MCP servers run over stdio, debugging can be challenging. For the best debugging\nexperience, we strongly recommend using the [MCP Inspector](https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/inspector).\n\nYou can launch the MCP Inspector with this command:\n\n```bash\nbun run inspector\n```\n\nUpon launching, the Inspector will display a URL that you can access in your browser to begin debugging.\n\n## License\n\nMIT License - see [LICENSE](LICENSE) file for details."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":960,"aggregated":"# Unity MCP Server\n\nMCP server to connect Claude with Unity projects. Built using the [Model Context Protocol SDK](https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/typescript-sdk).\n\n## Features\n- List all Unity projects \n- Get detailed project information\n- Access project structure and files\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Run this project locally\nRun this project locally by cloning this repo\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/your-username/unity-mcp.git\ncd unity-mcp\nbun install\n```\n\nAdd this tool as an MCP server in Claude.\n\nOn MacOS: `~/Library/Application\\ Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json`  \nOn Windows: `%APPDATA%/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"mcpServers\": {\n    \"unity\": {\n      \"command\": \"bun\",\n      \"args\": [\"run\", \"C:\\\\Users\\\\Artga\\\\Code\\\\unity-mcp\\\\src\\\\index.ts\"]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Requirements\n- Unity with projects configured\n- Bun runtime\n\n### Troubleshooting\nPlease open an issue if you can't get this MCP working. Here are some tips:\n1. Make sure Unity is installed and you have some projects configured\n2. Check that the unity-mcp server can access the projects-v1.json file\n3. Ensure you have proper permissions for the Unity project directories\n\nThis MCP will emit logs to stderr as specified in the MCP spec. On Mac the Claude Desktop app should emit these logs\nto `~/Library/Logs/Claude`. \nOn other platforms [you can find logs here](https://modelcontextprotocol.io/quickstart/user#getting-logs-from-claude-for-desktop).\n\n## Development\n\n### Setup\n```bash\n# Install dependencies\nbun install\n\n# Run the project\nbun run src/index.ts\n\n# Type check\nbun run typecheck\n\n# Format code\nbun run format\n```\n\n### Debugging\n\nSince MCP servers run over stdio, debugging can be challenging. For the best debugging\nexperience, we strongly recommend using the [MCP Inspector](https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/inspector).\n\nYou can launch the MCP Inspector with this command:\n\n```bash\nbun run inspector\n```\n\nUpon launching, the Inspector will display a URL that you can access in your browser to begin debugging.\n\n## License\n\nMIT License - see [LICENSE](LICENSE) file for details.","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779787959065}}
{"type":"message","id":"75579e11","parentId":"8b1adf74","timestamp":"2026-05-26T09:32:45.570Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This `unity-mcp` package (v1.1.0 by artmann) is much simpler - it just lists projects and structure, not actual editor control. Not what the user wants.\n\nThe `@akiojin/unity-mcp-server` is the right one. But I notice the npm package I downloaded (v5.5.2) is just the server-side MCP server. The Unity Editor plugin needs to be installed separately via UPM (Unity Package Manager) from the git URL.\n\nLet me provide the user with:\n1. The downloaded npm package (server component)\n2. Instructions for both parts\n\nActually, I should also check if maybe the user just wants me to try to install the Unity-side plugin via UPM. But I can't interact with Unity's UI directly. Let me present what I have.\n\nLet me also clean up the test file.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"搞定了！下载到了 **`@akiojin/unity-mcp-server` v5.5.2**，这个明确支持 **Unity 2020.3 LTS+**。\n\n已下载 npm 包：\n- `C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\akiojin-unity-mcp-server-5.5.2.tgz`\n\n**安装需要两部分：**\n\n### 1️⃣ Unity 端插件（UPM 安装）\n在 Unity 中打开 **Window → Package Manager → + → Add package from git URL**，输入：\n```\nhttps://github.com/akiojin/unity-mcp-server.git?path=UnityMCPServer/Packages/unity-mcp-server\n```\n\n### 2️⃣ MCP Server（Node.js）\n```bash\nnpm install -g @akiojin/unity-mcp-server\n```\n\n### 3️⃣ 配置 Claude Desktop\n在 `claude_desktop_config.json` 中添加：\n```json\n{\n  \"mcpServers\": {\n    \"unity-mcp-server\": {\n      \"command\": \"npx\",\n      \"args\": [\"@akiojin/unity-mcp-server@latest\"]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n重启 Claude Desktop，然后在 Unity 里打开项目就能用了。\n\n要我现在把 Unity 端插件也下载下来，或者直接在 Claude Desktop 上帮你配置一部分吗？🌸"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_M7eXdzxERaZCHSCqLafF2662","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"del C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\_search_github.mjs 2>NUL","timeout":5}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":589,"output":558,"cacheRead":139392,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":140539,"cost":{"input":0.00008246,"output":0.00015624,"cacheRead":0.003902976,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0041416759999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779787959067,"responseId":"bb59afd3-c5a1-4940-b2dc-5d97a9ccbc11"}}
