{"type":"message","id":"d2339de2","parentId":"56e20418","timestamp":"2026-05-26T09:37:45.502Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, I need to be careful here. Sending keyboard input to the Unity window might not work well with `SendKeys` since `SendKeys` sends to the active window, and `SetForegroundWindow` might not be sufficient to guarantee focus.\n\nAlso, there's a question of whether the user wants me to actually automate their Unity UI. This is a \"real\" interaction with the user's desktop environment. In AGENTS.md it says \"Ask first\" for things that leave the machine, but this is a local operation. Let me proceed.\n\nActually, let me also think about whether `Ctrl+P` is the right key. In Unity, Ctrl+P in Windows is indeed Play/Pause. Let me execute.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_P9dvkC3rweLT6BVgIYUc8217","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\_play_unity.ps1","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":89,"output":238,"cacheRead":147840,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":148167,"cost":{"input":0.000012460000000000001,"output":0.00006664,"cacheRead":0.00413952,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00421862}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779788260215,"responseId":"3275269a-9a63-4311-ab4c-9ee43dab628f"}}
